``` lang-java
List&lt;BeanA&gt; beanAs = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();

for (EntityA a : entityAs) {
    BeanA beanA = new BeanA();
    beanA.setName(a.getName());

    Map&lt;String, Object&gt; beanMap = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();
    beanMap.put(&quot;custom_column&quot;, a.getCustom_column());

    beanA.setBeanMap(beanMap);

    beanAs.add(beanA);
}
```

When you only ever have a map with a single entry, you could optimize the map creation to
``` lang-java
Map&lt;String, Object&gt; beanMap = 
        java.util.Collections.singletonMap(&quot;custom_column&quot;, a.getCustom_column());
// no beanMap.put... necessary
```

or if you use Java 9 or newer even shorter with
``` lang-java
Map&lt;String, Object&gt; beanMap = Map.of(&quot;custom_column&quot;, a.getCustom_column());
// no beanMap.put... necessary
```

