answers.body_markdown:
You&#39;re missing a default constructor for `ConnectionProperties` to instantiate the class and map the properties if missing.

Not sure if or how this could be translated to Lombok somehow with `@NoArgsConstructor` and `@AllArgsConstructor`, but this should work:

```java
@Configuration
@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = &quot;my.externalsystem&quot;)
@Getter
@Setter
public class MyConfiguration {

    private ConnectionProperties connection = new ConnectionProperties();

    @Getter
    @Setter
    public static class ConnectionProperties {
        private boolean enabled;

        public ConnectionProperties() {
            this.enabled = true;
        }
    }
}
```

In this example if the property is missing it will just use the default value from the constructor and will override it if the property is present.

